OL,3,CWar within a war: Yemini children
OL,4,Cstruggle for water in city under siege
OL,6,FBut this is serious work. In the fight
OL,7,Ffor survival in Taizz, no one is
OL,8,Fspared a role. It is often the
OL,9,Fyoungest who are sent to complete the
OL,10,Fchilling task of collecting water, on
OL,11,Fbehalf of their entire family to
OL,12,Fensure that no one dies from thirst.
OL,14,F"We are dying, we are dying," says
OL,15,FMajid, a local man who is among the
OL,16,Fdozens of cross-fingered Taizzis
OL,17,Fhoping that today a delivery will
OL,18,Farrive.
