OL,3,CWar within a war: Yemini children
OL,4,Cstruggle for water in city under siege
OL,6,FLike everyone else, he is clutching
OL,7,Fhis empty bottle which bears his name.
OL,8,FI ask him what the outside world can
OL,9,Fdo to help the situation.
OL,11,FHe pauses. "Stop the siege of Taizz.
OL,12,FStop the siege of Taizz."
OL,14,FAt the nearby hospital, the
OL,15,Fconsequences of the crisis are clear.
OL,16,FThe faint weeps of children can be
OL,17,Fheard as the doors to the malnutrition
OL,18,Fward open. But Aisha is silent.
