OL,3,CWar within a war: Yemini children
OL,4,Cstruggle for water in city under siege
OL,6,FAt her bedside is her aunt, Karema Al-
OL,7,FMamari, not her parents, who judged
OL,8,Fthe journey across the city to save
OL,9,Ftheir daughter to be too dangerous for
OL,10,Fher healthier siblings.
OL,12,FAn amateur singer, Karema performed at
OL,13,Fwedding ceremonies to raise money to
OL,14,Fcome to the clinic after struggling to
OL,15,Ffind food and medicine where she
OL,16,Flived. "We went by ourselves to get
OL,17,Fwater from the well because we don't
OL,18,Fhave any in our village. We carried
OL,19,Fwater with donkeys," she says.
