OL,3,CWar within a war: Yemini children
OL,4,Cstruggle for water in city under siege
OL,6,FTaizz is a war within a war within a
OL,7,Fwar. And we are looking at part of the
OL,8,Fmost dangerous dividing line in world
OL,9,Fpolitics.
OL,11,FBefore we leave the city, we return to
OL,12,Fsee Aisha. She had been lying on the
OL,13,Ffirst bed as you enter the ward.
OL,15,FBut as we approach down a short
OL,16,Fcorridor, her bed lies empty, apart
OL,17,Ffrom a simple cloth and her aunt's
OL,18,Fsimple mobile phone. It is an ominous
OL,19,Fmoment, given the bleak prognosis
OL,20,Fshared by the doctor the previous day.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G11/13
