OL,3,CWar within a war: Yemini children
OL,4,Cstruggle for water in city under siege
OL,6,FBut when we move into the ward, Aisha
OL,7,Fis there, struggling to sit up
OL,8,Fstraight on the scales, a task she was
OL,9,Fincapable of contemplating in the
OL,10,Fpreceding days.
OL,12,FIt is not a breakthrough, but she is
OL,13,Fresponding to treatment better than
OL,14,Fexpected. Her aunt hopes the doctors
OL,15,Fwere being too pessimistic.
OL,17,FShe asks her niece to look towards our
OL,18,Fcamera. "Tell them your name is Aisha
OL,19,Fand you want to go home."
